Hi @Mr-Grieves

A few additional questions:

  • Is there any warning or error message when calling converter.convert()?
  • If you try print(len(tflite_model)), what's the length of the binary bytes?
  • If the answer for the last question isn't 0, it may be the case that you didn't close the file so the content isn't flush out. Could you try to write the model like this?
with open("SEGNET.tflite", "wb") as f:
  f.write(tflite_model)

Thanks!

body:
Hi @Mr-Grieves 

A few additional questions:

* Is there any warning or error message when calling `converter.convert()`?
* If you try `print(len(tflite_model))`, what's the length of the binary bytes?
* If the answer for the last question isn't 0, it may be the case that you didn't close the file so the content isn't flush out. Could you try to write the model like this?

```
with open("SEGNET.tflite", "wb") as f:
  f.write(tflite_model)
```

Thanks!
